            <div class="staticBlurb">
              <p>Ady Gil is the co-founder of ShelterMe.com and an executive producer of the PBS series, <span style="font-weight:bold;">SHELTER ME</span>. He is recognized as one of the most influential and generous philanthropists in the animal welfare movement today. His funding and support has enabled countless rescue and humane organizations to continue their life saving work worldwide. Ady’s dedication on behalf of animals has been recognized in multiple media outlets including CNN, The New York Times, The Los Angeles Times and Forbes Magazine. He is also the recipient of numerous, prestigious humane awards from animal organizations both large and small. </p>
              <p>Ady’s more notable achievements include the rescue and placement of thousands of dogs from inhumane puppy mills into loving homes, the purchase of a ship called ‘The Ady Gil’ which prevented the slaughter of whales from Japan to the Antarctic sea, all while he continues to work with governmental agencies and policy makers to create groundbreaking laws to protect animals.</p>
              <p>He founded the companies American Hi Definition and Sweetwater Digital, which he recently sold so he could live his life-long dream of helping animals full time. Ady enjoys spending time with his rescue dog, Kayla, and rescue cat, Ozzy.</p>
